1
00:00:18,184 --> 00:00:19,519
[Joe] Previously on You:

2
00:00:19,602 --> 00:00:22,022
Love, what did you do?

3
00:00:22,564 --> 00:00:24,482
We bury her in the woods.

4
00:00:24,566 --> 00:00:26,443
Love, this is my son, Theo.

5
00:00:26,526 --> 00:00:29,779
-I didn't know you had a son.
-Stepson from my first marriage.

6
00:00:29,863 --> 00:00:31,865
I got the twins wearing those Vital Rings.

7
00:00:31,948 --> 00:00:34,409
-Does this have GPS?
-[Cary] We all wear them.

8
00:00:34,492 --> 00:00:36,244
[Joe] If Matthew has access
to Natalie's ring,

9
00:00:36,327 --> 00:00:38,872
he'll be able to see exactly where she is.

10
00:00:38,955 --> 00:00:42,542
I put the ring on the sink
so it looked like she washed her hands.

11
00:00:43,418 --> 00:00:46,629
So... they know.

12
00:00:47,297 --> 00:00:49,674
[Joe] We've got this. Together.

13
00:01:00,351 --> 00:01:02,103
[Henry crying]

14
00:01:02,187 --> 00:01:04,564
[Joe]
Things are always better in the morning.

15
00:01:04,647 --> 00:01:05,982
[pop music playing]

16
00:01:06,066 --> 00:01:08,526
At least that's what Scout tells us.

17
00:01:15,658 --> 00:01:19,204
And who am I to argue with Harper Lee?

18
00:01:21,873 --> 00:01:23,750
Then again, Scout didn't help

19
00:01:23,833 --> 00:01:27,087
to cover up the murder
of the next-door neighbor's wife.

20
00:01:30,256 --> 00:01:33,968
Here, in Madre Linda,
safest neighborhood in the Golden State,

21
00:01:34,052 --> 00:01:37,138
every passing morning brings
more attention.

22
00:01:38,014 --> 00:01:40,475
A woman has disappeared.

23
00:01:41,059 --> 00:01:45,396
It's domestic noir come to life,
and people are here for it.

24
00:01:45,480 --> 00:01:46,731
Keep it going.

25
00:01:46,815 --> 00:01:48,191
Hold, hold, hold.

26
00:01:49,192 --> 00:01:50,026
Squeeze glutes.

27
00:01:50,110 --> 00:01:51,152
[cell phone beeps]

28
00:01:51,236 --> 00:01:52,070
Starting.

29
00:01:53,071 --> 00:01:57,408
It's been three days since the sleepy town
of Madre Linda was rocked

30
00:01:57,492 --> 00:02:00,161
by the disappearance of Natalie Engler.

31
00:02:00,245 --> 00:02:04,040
The 32-year-old realtor was last seen
leaving her home for work.

32
00:02:04,124 --> 00:02:08,086
Her vehicle was found outside
a cabin near Redwoods State Park.

33
00:02:08,962 --> 00:02:10,255
-Ready, sweetie?
-Yeah.

34
00:02:10,338 --> 00:02:11,756
All right, here we go.

35
00:02:13,967 --> 00:02:16,803
[Goodwin] Her husband,
tech entrepreneur Matthew Engler,

36
00:02:16,886 --> 00:02:19,889
who made his fortune
in cutting-edge surveillance,

37
00:02:19,973 --> 00:02:21,891
has not made a public statement.

38
00:02:21,975 --> 00:02:24,018
God, I hope she just ran off somewhere.

39
00:02:24,602 --> 00:02:26,980
For now, friends are hopeful

40
00:02:27,063 --> 00:02:30,942
that the police will find her
with the help of this community.

41
00:02:31,025 --> 00:02:34,737
Reporting live from Madre Linda,
Ryan Goodwin, Channel 3 News.

42
00:02:35,446 --> 00:02:36,656
We got it.

43
00:02:36,739 --> 00:02:39,117
Every day it's the same fucking story.

44
00:02:40,410 --> 00:02:42,328
We need him to give a statement.

45
00:02:47,250 --> 00:02:49,169
[dramatic music playing]

46
00:02:55,675 --> 00:02:58,761
And our son is mercifully
once again sleeping.

47
00:02:59,762 --> 00:03:03,308
-Can I make you some eggs?
-There's more vans than yesterday.

48
00:03:03,850 --> 00:03:05,643
I wish they'd move on already.

49
00:03:05,727 --> 00:03:07,228
[Joe] You are worried.

50
00:03:07,312 --> 00:03:08,897
I'm sure they will. Soon.

51
00:03:08,980 --> 00:03:12,483
Your previous mistakes were cleaned up
by the family fixer.

52
00:03:12,567 --> 00:03:16,029
No media or police to deal with
when they've been paid off.

53
00:03:16,112 --> 00:03:18,865
When do you think
everything will die down?

54
00:03:18,948 --> 00:03:21,201
A week, maybe two.

55
00:03:21,284 --> 00:03:23,411
How can you be so calm?

56
00:03:23,494 --> 00:03:27,749
[Joe] Experience. Try killing
a celebrity comedian without a fixer.

57
00:03:27,832 --> 00:03:28,666
Joe.

58
00:03:31,544 --> 00:03:32,503
I'm scared.

59
00:03:32,587 --> 00:03:35,465
Dr. Chandra said
that we should give words to our emotions.

60
00:03:35,548 --> 00:03:36,507
Well, I'm...

61
00:03:37,508 --> 00:03:38,718
scared.

62
00:03:42,222 --> 00:03:44,474
I'm not gonna let anything bad happen.

63
00:03:44,557 --> 00:03:46,434
We have done everything right.

64
00:03:46,517 --> 00:03:50,271
But the ring?
That was a close call, but we fixed it.

65
00:03:50,355 --> 00:03:51,856
We talked to the cops.

66
00:03:52,482 --> 00:03:54,234
They didn't raise an eyebrow.

67
00:03:54,317 --> 00:03:55,693
This won't take long.

68
00:03:56,319 --> 00:03:58,988
Is there anything
you can tell us about Natalie Engler

69
00:03:59,072 --> 00:04:01,491
or her relationship with her husband?

70
00:04:01,574 --> 00:04:04,535
We just moved here
a few months ago with a newborn,

71
00:04:04,619 --> 00:04:07,830
so we haven't had much time
for socializing.

72
00:04:08,414 --> 00:04:12,752
Yeah. She did help me lease my bakery,
but other than that,

73
00:04:12,835 --> 00:04:14,420
I don't really know them.

74
00:04:14,504 --> 00:04:17,507
-I wish we could tell you more.
-Can I refill your coffee?

75
00:04:18,758 --> 00:04:21,469
Of course they're not gonna act
like they're suspicious.

76
00:04:21,552 --> 00:04:25,348
True. But we haven't given them
a reason to be suspicious. What?

77
00:04:25,431 --> 00:04:27,392
[reporters clamoring]

78
00:04:27,475 --> 00:04:28,726
A few questions, sir.

79
00:04:28,810 --> 00:04:31,729
Matthew, Channel 6.
A quick statement, please.

80
00:04:33,064 --> 00:04:34,274
Hey, hey.

81
00:04:34,983 --> 00:04:35,900
Look.

82
00:04:35,984 --> 00:04:37,610
[Goodwin] Have the police said anything?

83
00:04:37,694 --> 00:04:39,696
Get off my property
or I'll have you removed.

84
00:04:39,779 --> 00:04:42,073
-[Goodwin] Matthew, statement.
-[man] Can you say something?

85
00:04:42,156 --> 00:04:47,996
He's innocent, but he's acting guilty.
That's strange but... good.

86
00:04:48,079 --> 00:04:51,249
Good for us.
If he goes down for this, we're free.

87
00:04:51,332 --> 00:04:53,251
[Joe] You're doing
your Lady Macbeth thing again.

88
00:04:53,334 --> 00:04:55,753
Like when you wanted
to frame Ellie for killing Hendy.

89
00:04:55,837 --> 00:04:58,047
You feel trapped
and it's clouding your judgment.

90
00:04:58,131 --> 00:05:00,633
It's probably best
if no one goes down for this, right?

91
00:05:00,717 --> 00:05:05,972
Like, if nobody finds the body,
people will eventually assume she ran off.

92
00:05:06,597 --> 00:05:07,849
Yeah. You're right.

93
00:05:09,809 --> 00:05:11,769
What are we supposed to do
in the meantime?

94
00:05:16,149 --> 00:05:17,108
This.

95
00:05:17,692 --> 00:05:22,155
Just normal life.
We keep watching the news, just in case.

96
00:05:23,114 --> 00:05:24,115
We go to work.

97
00:05:25,700 --> 00:05:27,076
We take care of Henry.

98
00:05:30,913 --> 00:05:32,915
I'll keep us safe, I promise.

99
00:05:33,499 --> 00:05:34,459
So...

100
00:05:36,169 --> 00:05:37,670
just be normal.

101
00:05:37,754 --> 00:05:38,713
Exactly.

102
00:05:40,381 --> 00:05:43,176
Something terrible happened
to Natalie Engler.

103
00:05:43,676 --> 00:05:45,386
We had nothing to do with it.

104
00:05:45,970 --> 00:05:50,433
We are just the nice,
normal neighbors next door.

105
00:05:59,609 --> 00:06:02,320
[Joe] Crying for the camera isn't
for everyone, fine.

106
00:06:02,403 --> 00:06:04,238
But he's just working.

107
00:06:04,322 --> 00:06:07,200
I know why I'm acting normal,
but why is he?

108
00:06:09,410 --> 00:06:14,082
Fuck. The last thing I need is
to inspire him to start watching me.

109
00:06:20,004 --> 00:06:21,047
[doorbell ringing]

110
00:06:21,130 --> 00:06:24,592
-Look! Grandma's here!
-Thank you, Mustafa. Ciao.

111
00:06:25,426 --> 00:06:27,512
Why were you talking to our trust lawyer?

112
00:06:27,595 --> 00:06:30,390
Dreadful divorce nonsense.
Don't get me started.

113
00:06:30,473 --> 00:06:34,102
Is that woman still missing?
I had to park two streets over.

114
00:06:34,185 --> 00:06:36,562
-Come here, my darling, my darling.
-[Henry crying]

115
00:06:36,646 --> 00:06:40,441
Glamma missed you. Glamma missed you.
Glamma missed you.

116
00:06:40,525 --> 00:06:45,071
I'm sure the husband did it.
You have to watch out for husbands.

117
00:06:45,154 --> 00:06:46,864
Ray would love to have me killed.

118
00:06:46,948 --> 00:06:48,991
You know,
that's if I don't have him killed first.

119
00:06:49,075 --> 00:06:51,452
-[chuckles]
-I assume there's coffee.

120
00:06:52,036 --> 00:06:54,705
Let me get some coffee. Yeah. Yeah.

121
00:06:59,168 --> 00:07:02,088
-Do you think he's warm?
-I think he's just tired.

122
00:07:03,464 --> 00:07:04,924
Maybe I should stay.

123
00:07:06,050 --> 00:07:08,136
You're projecting
your anxiety on your son.

124
00:07:08,219 --> 00:07:09,595
Go run your bakery.

125
00:07:11,013 --> 00:07:13,516
Forty and I are gonna have
a beautiful day.

126
00:07:13,599 --> 00:07:15,768
♪ Baby, baby ♪

127
00:07:15,852 --> 00:07:16,978
[Dottie humming]

128
00:07:21,691 --> 00:07:22,984
[groaning]

129
00:07:28,531 --> 00:07:30,283
[pop music playing over speakers]

130
00:07:35,288 --> 00:07:36,914
[bells chiming]

131
00:07:38,124 --> 00:07:40,084
Hey, guys. What can I get you?

132
00:07:40,168 --> 00:07:43,212
Thanks for asking.
But we're here as concerned citizens.

133
00:07:43,296 --> 00:07:45,465
We started the committee
to find Natalie Engler.

134
00:07:45,548 --> 00:07:48,509
Did she ever say anything to you
about wanting to run away?

135
00:07:48,593 --> 00:07:50,261
Or being scared of creepy Matthew?

136
00:07:50,344 --> 00:07:52,180
Um, uh...

137
00:07:52,263 --> 00:07:53,181
No.

138
00:07:55,641 --> 00:07:57,185
Don't you think this is premature?

139
00:07:57,268 --> 00:07:59,770
-We don't know if anything bad--
-Matter of time.

140
00:07:59,854 --> 00:08:02,648
Oh, my God, have you seen
the Tracy Paulson murder docuseries?

141
00:08:02,732 --> 00:08:05,526
I have. Spoiler alert, it's the husband.

142
00:08:05,610 --> 00:08:07,278
-Always the husband.
-[Kiki] Always.

143
00:08:07,361 --> 00:08:09,906
I heard Matthew wasn't even
the first to call the police.

144
00:08:09,989 --> 00:08:11,991
-Her sister did.
-Love.

145
00:08:13,201 --> 00:08:15,745
Have you ever heard Natalie
and Matthew fighting?

146
00:08:15,828 --> 00:08:16,913
[ominous music playing]

147
00:08:20,208 --> 00:08:22,043
Joe and I barely know them.

148
00:08:22,126 --> 00:08:26,547
She showed me this place
shortly before, you know--

149
00:08:26,631 --> 00:08:29,759
This must be so difficult for you.

150
00:08:31,636 --> 00:08:32,845
Thank you.

151
00:08:32,929 --> 00:08:36,641
Honestly, the only thing I can do
to feel normal is come here.

152
00:08:37,683 --> 00:08:38,518
And...

153
00:08:41,020 --> 00:08:43,064
these keto vanilla bean scones.

154
00:08:46,234 --> 00:08:48,027
Sure you don't want one?

155
00:08:50,196 --> 00:08:53,741
-Why not? Oh.
-I would love a couple.

156
00:08:53,824 --> 00:08:58,287
Brandon is coming off of an IF,
so this will be a nice treat for him.

157
00:09:05,545 --> 00:09:09,799
End of each day, check tables
and study carrels for re-shelves.

158
00:09:09,882 --> 00:09:11,634
That's where they go until the last...

159
00:09:11,717 --> 00:09:15,805
[Joe] Somehow, I chose
the perfect place to be normal in.

160
00:09:15,888 --> 00:09:19,058
An oasis of unpretentious regular people.

161
00:09:20,101 --> 00:09:21,602
I love it here.

162
00:09:22,520 --> 00:09:23,479
Hello?

163
00:09:24,146 --> 00:09:27,358
[Joe] My grown-up hall monitor
of a boss notwithstanding.

164
00:09:27,441 --> 00:09:28,442
Sorry about that.

165
00:09:28,526 --> 00:09:33,322
I have to say, I'm still very unclear
as to why you decided to volunteer here.

166
00:09:33,864 --> 00:09:36,284
Unless you're one of those parents

167
00:09:36,367 --> 00:09:39,453
trying to pad a nonexistent
community-service résumé

168
00:09:39,537 --> 00:09:41,747
to get his kid
into one of the top schools.

169
00:09:41,831 --> 00:09:43,165
[Joe] Is she psychic?

170
00:09:43,958 --> 00:09:45,126
Mm-hm.

171
00:09:47,670 --> 00:09:50,673
Hey, Dante. This is Joe.

172
00:09:50,756 --> 00:09:52,925
[Joe] Dante Ferguson. Former Navy.

173
00:09:53,009 --> 00:09:56,721
One hundred percent blind.
Longtime friend of my new stern boss.

174
00:09:56,804 --> 00:10:00,141
Dante will be your go-to
for any questions. He knows all.

175
00:10:00,224 --> 00:10:03,769
All-knowing Dante's listening
to the news. It's about Natalie Engler.

176
00:10:03,853 --> 00:10:04,770
[Joe] Oh, no.

177
00:10:04,854 --> 00:10:06,981
Madre Linda has
her own Missing White Woman.

178
00:10:07,064 --> 00:10:11,360
Missing White Woman Syndrome is
America's favorite pastime next to porn.

179
00:10:11,444 --> 00:10:14,989
-Missing White Woman...?
-Syndrome.

180
00:10:15,072 --> 00:10:18,075
When upper-class,
attractive white ladies go missing,

181
00:10:18,159 --> 00:10:20,077
they get tons of media coverage.

182
00:10:20,161 --> 00:10:22,913
-Doesn't happen for other victims.
-Yeah.

183
00:10:22,997 --> 00:10:27,168
Well, the media has a thirst
for anything salacious, right?

184
00:10:29,503 --> 00:10:31,380
Why do I feel like I'm failing a test?

185
00:10:31,464 --> 00:10:33,299
We're speaking of a specific phenomenon.

186
00:10:33,966 --> 00:10:36,761
When white women receive
disproportionately high attention,

187
00:10:36,844 --> 00:10:38,638
a clear message is being sent.

188
00:10:38,721 --> 00:10:43,225
White ladies deserve to be rescued.
The rest of us can fend for ourselves.

189
00:10:43,809 --> 00:10:45,519
Agreed. Obviously.

190
00:10:45,603 --> 00:10:47,521
I'm not sure why you're saying "obviously"

191
00:10:47,605 --> 00:10:49,982
when you didn't even know
about the phenomenon.

192
00:10:50,566 --> 00:10:52,777
Mm. She got you there, beanpole.

193
00:10:52,860 --> 00:10:55,696
-[Joe] How does he know I--?
-[Marienne] Tender is the Night.

194
00:10:55,780 --> 00:10:57,114
You knew her.

195
00:10:57,698 --> 00:10:58,949
-We're neighbors.
-Shush.

196
00:10:59,033 --> 00:11:01,369
They're about to interview her friend.

197
00:11:01,452 --> 00:11:04,080
-Mind if I have a bathroom break?
-Bathroom's that way.

198
00:11:04,163 --> 00:11:05,414
-Thank you.
-Mm-hm.

199
00:11:10,086 --> 00:11:12,797
-Dante, kill me now.
-Is he cute?

200
00:11:14,090 --> 00:11:15,216
[Joe] Are you kidding me?

201
00:11:15,299 --> 00:11:17,051
[Sherry on video] We set up a tip line,

202
00:11:17,134 --> 00:11:19,428
and you can follow us
on Facebook, Twitter,

203
00:11:19,512 --> 00:11:21,931
Insta, Snapchat, TikTok, and Tumblr.

204
00:11:22,014 --> 00:11:24,600
For those of you
that are still using that.

205
00:11:24,684 --> 00:11:27,687
Finding Natalie seems
incredibly important to you.

206
00:11:27,770 --> 00:11:34,151
Oh, my God, it's my number one priority.
Natalie was my dearest and closest friend.

207
00:11:34,235 --> 00:11:35,444
[Joe] She hated her.

208
00:11:35,528 --> 00:11:37,196
[Sherry] We all loved her.

209
00:11:37,655 --> 00:11:41,117
I'm not really sure why
her husband hasn't told you this,

210
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:44,578
but I think the public would like
to hear from him.

211
00:11:44,662 --> 00:11:48,165
[Joe] And she just slipped in
a Matthew dig on live television.

212
00:11:48,249 --> 00:11:50,084
Bitchy, but not the worst thing for us.

213
00:11:50,167 --> 00:11:52,211
[Goodwin]
Why do you think Natalie's disappearance

214
00:11:52,294 --> 00:11:54,630
has struck such a chord in this community?

215
00:11:54,714 --> 00:12:00,136
Natalie is a woman who cares deeply
for this town and everyone in it.

216
00:12:00,219 --> 00:12:02,722
In fact, one of the last things she did

217
00:12:02,805 --> 00:12:06,183
was lease a space for a bakery
for her next-door neighbor.

218
00:12:06,267 --> 00:12:07,893
She lives right over there.

219
00:12:07,977 --> 00:12:10,521
[Joe] Did Sherry Conrad just tell
the entire world

220
00:12:10,604 --> 00:12:14,817
that one of the last people who saw
the Missing White Woman was my wife?

221
00:12:14,900 --> 00:12:18,112
I have to reassure you.
Everything is fine. Still fine.

222
00:12:18,195 --> 00:12:19,947
-[cell phone buzzing]
-Who the hell is this?

223
00:12:21,532 --> 00:12:22,366
Hello?

224
00:12:25,035 --> 00:12:28,247
Hi. Yeah, absolutely.
What can I do for you, detective?

225
00:12:28,330 --> 00:12:29,623
Fuck me.

226
00:12:33,753 --> 00:12:35,629
[Falco] When we spoke
to you and your wife,

227
00:12:35,713 --> 00:12:37,131
you said you barely knew Natalie.

228
00:12:37,214 --> 00:12:38,716
Yeah. Yeah, that's true.

229
00:12:39,467 --> 00:12:41,469
Then why is there security footage

230
00:12:41,552 --> 00:12:44,472
of you two chatting
in a grocery store parking lot

231
00:12:44,555 --> 00:12:46,182
two days before she vanished?

232
00:12:46,891 --> 00:12:49,769
[Joe] Sweating? I need to get it together.

233
00:12:51,896 --> 00:12:55,232
Coincidence. I like to say hi
when I run into a neighbor.

234
00:12:55,316 --> 00:12:57,234
How do you explain...

235
00:12:58,778 --> 00:13:00,279
this exchange?

236
00:13:00,362 --> 00:13:03,157
[Joe] Does every inch of Madre Linda
have a camera?

237
00:13:03,949 --> 00:13:06,786
Do you typically receive prophylactics
from your neighbors

238
00:13:06,869 --> 00:13:08,913
when you just stop to say hi?

239
00:13:09,830 --> 00:13:12,458
[Joe] They don't suspect me.
They are just doing their job.

240
00:13:12,541 --> 00:13:14,168
I need to stop sweating.

241
00:13:14,251 --> 00:13:15,753
[cell phone buzzing]

242
00:13:16,837 --> 00:13:21,091
-You can deal with that if you need to.
-[Joe] So they can observe my behavior.

243
00:13:21,175 --> 00:13:22,760
No, it's fine. It's okay.

244
00:13:23,677 --> 00:13:24,845
Condoms...

245
00:13:25,429 --> 00:13:28,307
The thing is,
Natalie has a weird sense of humor,

246
00:13:28,390 --> 00:13:30,017
