498
00:28:30,875 --> 00:28:33,712
Some fucking brain-dead anti-vaxxer
got him sick,

499
00:28:33,795 --> 00:28:36,506
and it's probably getting
other people infected

500
00:28:36,589 --> 00:28:40,885
with some horrible life-threatening virus
that shouldn't even be a thing anymore.

501
00:28:40,969 --> 00:28:42,303
Hey, hey, hey.

502
00:28:44,389 --> 00:28:45,390
It's okay.

503
00:28:47,559 --> 00:28:49,728
-I'm sorry.
-Hey. Mm-mm.

504
00:28:50,311 --> 00:28:51,980
You don't have to apologize.

505
00:28:52,814 --> 00:28:54,607
Oh. I locked up the store.

506
00:28:54,691 --> 00:28:57,777
It was a really nice distraction
from being at home.

507
00:28:57,861 --> 00:29:00,321
Until the news crew arrived.

508
00:29:00,405 --> 00:29:01,406
Mm.

509
00:29:02,407 --> 00:29:04,784
Uh, when are you going back to school?

510
00:29:04,868 --> 00:29:07,370
Uh, I don't know. I feel like...

511
00:29:07,454 --> 00:29:10,790
we should probably wait
until we know about Natalie.

512
00:29:10,874 --> 00:29:16,463
So if you need some cheap-to-free labor
at the bakery,

513
00:29:17,088 --> 00:29:18,423
I'm your guy.

514
00:29:18,506 --> 00:29:20,425
Yeah, come in whenever you want.

515
00:29:21,718 --> 00:29:23,011
I could use the help.

516
00:29:24,512 --> 00:29:25,346
Okay.

517
00:29:26,556 --> 00:29:28,099
That would be great. Yeah.

518
00:29:28,183 --> 00:29:30,852
Especially if it gets me away
from my dad. Even better.

519
00:29:32,061 --> 00:29:34,147
He's really that hard to live with?

520
00:29:35,023 --> 00:29:35,982
Yeah.

521
00:29:36,065 --> 00:29:38,443
He's just never really been
a communicator,

522
00:29:38,526 --> 00:29:40,779
but, you know, his wife's missing.

523
00:29:40,862 --> 00:29:42,280
So if there was a time

524
00:29:42,363 --> 00:29:45,742
to start expressing
some form of emotion, it's now.

525
00:29:45,825 --> 00:29:49,370
But he's not.
He's, like, totally closed off.

526
00:29:49,454 --> 00:29:51,748
I don't know.
I just feel like it's gonna make him,

527
00:29:51,831 --> 00:29:54,125
like, even that more unreachable.

528
00:29:58,713 --> 00:29:59,839
You okay?

529
00:30:00,715 --> 00:30:02,217
-[Katzir] Ms. Quinn-Goldberg?
-Yes.

530
00:30:02,300 --> 00:30:04,719
-A moment?
-Yes. Thank you.

531
00:30:04,803 --> 00:30:06,930
-Thank you.
-[stammers] Yeah, of course.

532
00:30:15,605 --> 00:30:17,732
[Joe] How did I end up here?

533
00:30:17,816 --> 00:30:22,278
Oh, I was coming here to hide the scarf.
Did he catch me trying to hide it?

534
00:30:22,362 --> 00:30:23,363
I'm sick.

535
00:30:24,364 --> 00:30:26,324
I was having a fever dream.

536
00:30:27,408 --> 00:30:30,453
I must have hopped your fence.

537
00:30:31,704 --> 00:30:32,747
[coughing]

538
00:30:35,124 --> 00:30:36,376
I've got the measles.

539
00:30:36,459 --> 00:30:38,753
-So you really--
-I've been immunized.

540
00:30:39,629 --> 00:30:40,964
Surprised you weren't.

541
00:30:41,047 --> 00:30:43,299
[Joe] It's like he's waiting for me
to give myself away.

542
00:30:43,383 --> 00:30:46,177
What would
a normal neighbor say right now?

543
00:30:46,261 --> 00:30:48,179
Yeah, me too. I should've known.

544
00:30:48,263 --> 00:30:52,475
I have a few gaps in my childhood.

545
00:30:56,563 --> 00:30:58,147
I'm sorry about your wife.

546
00:30:59,065 --> 00:31:03,528
I considered coming over,
but I didn't wanna bother you.

547
00:31:05,238 --> 00:31:07,574
There's that look again.

548
00:31:07,657 --> 00:31:09,450
Does he know I kissed Natalie?

549
00:31:09,534 --> 00:31:11,828
Is he the reason the police are up my ass?

550
00:31:11,911 --> 00:31:15,498
-Natalie said you were becoming friends.
-[Joe] Shit.

551
00:31:15,582 --> 00:31:17,625
-You had a glass of wine.
-[Joe] Game over.

552
00:31:17,709 --> 00:31:21,296
Did she say anything to you
about going to visit her sister?

553
00:31:21,379 --> 00:31:23,590
[Joe] Or he doesn't know anything.

554
00:31:23,673 --> 00:31:26,259
He's just hoping
I can help him find his missing wife.

555
00:31:26,342 --> 00:31:27,510
I'm sorry.

556
00:31:28,136 --> 00:31:30,054
She didn't mention it.

557
00:31:31,431 --> 00:31:33,474
-[coughing]
-You should rest.

558
00:31:33,558 --> 00:31:36,311
I gave you some Tylenol
to help bring down the fever.

559
00:31:36,895 --> 00:31:39,355
[Joe] Is it possible Matthew's a nice guy?

560
00:31:39,439 --> 00:31:40,273
Thank you.

561
00:31:43,568 --> 00:31:44,611
Sure.

562
00:31:51,409 --> 00:31:55,121
-There's no updates on my son.
-What's wrong with your son?

563
00:31:55,747 --> 00:31:57,248
He's sick too.

564
00:31:57,332 --> 00:31:58,958
He's in the hospital.

565
00:32:00,960 --> 00:32:02,754
What if he doesn't get better?

566
00:32:03,755 --> 00:32:07,759
What if they get punished for our sins?

567
00:32:12,013 --> 00:32:13,014
I think...

568
00:32:14,057 --> 00:32:16,225
it's not punishment, it's...

569
00:32:16,809 --> 00:32:20,563
They reflect our sins back at us
so clearly, it's blinding.

570
00:32:22,148 --> 00:32:24,734
I never saw myself becoming a father.

571
00:32:25,318 --> 00:32:28,696
Then I met Theo's mom.
People become dads all kinds of ways.

572
00:32:28,780 --> 00:32:31,574
I was even kind of excited about it,
and Theo was a great kid.

573
00:32:31,658 --> 00:32:35,828
But I was young and extremely ambitious.

574
00:32:37,580 --> 00:32:40,333
I was a shitty stepdad
and he hated me for it.

575
00:32:43,878 --> 00:32:47,006
But now his mom's remarried, new family,
and Theo hates her even more.

576
00:32:47,090 --> 00:32:49,050
He's come back here almost by default.

577
00:32:49,717 --> 00:32:52,136
Most of the time,
I still have no idea what I'm doing.

578
00:32:52,845 --> 00:32:54,931
All I know is that he needs me.

579
00:32:56,182 --> 00:32:59,936
He needs me on some primal level,
just like your son needs you.

580
00:33:07,026 --> 00:33:10,071
Are you sure Natalie didn't say anything
to you about taking a trip?

581
00:33:10,863 --> 00:33:11,823
I'm sure she's fine.

582
00:33:11,906 --> 00:33:15,326
She's done this for attention,
and she's too embarrassed to come home.

583
00:33:16,536 --> 00:33:19,080
You don't think
anything's happened to her, do you?

584
00:33:19,163 --> 00:33:21,791
[Joe] What have we done, Love?

585
00:33:21,874 --> 00:33:24,794
I wanna help, but safest thing

586
00:33:24,877 --> 00:33:29,048
is to let him stay silent and hang himself
in the court of public opinion.

587
00:33:29,132 --> 00:33:30,800
[cell phone buzzing]

588
00:33:35,513 --> 00:33:36,514
He's okay.

589
00:33:38,099 --> 00:33:40,727
-He's gonna be okay.
-That's good.

590
00:33:40,810 --> 00:33:42,270
[Joe] Henry's okay.

591
00:33:43,688 --> 00:33:45,940
And I promised him
I'd be a good man, worthy.

592
00:33:46,024 --> 00:33:49,027
I cannot frame an innocent man.
I can't do it.

593
00:33:50,486 --> 00:33:52,280
I'd be killing a mockingbird.

594
00:33:54,157 --> 00:33:57,452
I know that you love Natalie,
but you're not talking to the press.

595
00:33:57,535 --> 00:34:00,246
-I don't care about the press.
-You should.

596
00:34:00,329 --> 00:34:03,166
If you don't tell your story,
they will tell it for you.

597
00:34:03,249 --> 00:34:06,085
You can't be there for Theo
if you're behind bars.

598
00:34:13,843 --> 00:34:14,844
[door closes]

599
00:34:18,890 --> 00:34:19,724
Hey.

600
00:34:19,807 --> 00:34:21,059
Oh, hey.

601
00:34:21,142 --> 00:34:26,064
Oh, no, no.
I didn't realize you were sick too.

602
00:34:26,147 --> 00:34:29,609
-You poor thing.
-It's okay. It's okay. I'm recovering.

603
00:34:29,692 --> 00:34:32,987
-How is he?
-He misses his daddy.

604
00:34:35,740 --> 00:34:39,577
Don't ever scare us like that again,
Mr. Dramatic.

605
00:34:41,370 --> 00:34:42,789
I love you too much.

606
00:34:46,125 --> 00:34:47,460
Did you do it?

607
00:34:48,377 --> 00:34:51,547
[Joe] What you're really asking is
what kind of father I am.

608
00:34:51,631 --> 00:34:53,716
Wish you could go through the front.

609
00:34:53,800 --> 00:34:55,802
-Reporters, I get it.
-Yeah.

610
00:34:55,885 --> 00:34:58,971
-You sure I can't help you home?
-I'm okay. I'm okay.

611
00:34:59,055 --> 00:35:01,099
My wife and kid are coming back.

612
00:35:01,182 --> 00:35:04,644
-You've done more than enough.
-Okay. Get home safe.

613
00:35:05,353 --> 00:35:07,730
Don't wanna find you passed out
by the trash again.

614
00:35:10,608 --> 00:35:11,609
Mm.

615
00:35:14,612 --> 00:35:16,155
[ominous music playing]

616
00:35:29,377 --> 00:35:30,294
I did it.

617
00:35:31,629 --> 00:35:32,797
But then...

618
00:35:35,508 --> 00:35:36,801
I took it back.

619
00:35:37,510 --> 00:35:39,178
Matthew's a decent man.

620
00:35:39,262 --> 00:35:42,682
He already lost his wife.
If we send him to prison--

621
00:35:42,765 --> 00:35:44,517
What kind of people would we be?

622
00:35:44,600 --> 00:35:45,685
[Joe] Wow.

623
00:35:46,477 --> 00:35:47,562
You get it.

624
00:35:48,563 --> 00:35:49,939
We're better than that.

625
00:35:50,523 --> 00:35:52,567
["I Lied" playing]

626
00:35:52,650 --> 00:35:53,568
We are.

627
00:35:58,990 --> 00:36:02,285
What does it mean to be a good father?

628
00:36:02,368 --> 00:36:03,494
To protect, yes.

629
00:36:03,578 --> 00:36:05,830
But can you be a good father

630
00:36:05,913 --> 00:36:07,582
if you're a bad man?

631
00:36:08,166 --> 00:36:11,544
It's not the kind of father I wanna be
and the kind of mother you wanna be.

632
00:36:11,627 --> 00:36:12,461
Thank God.

633
00:36:13,379 --> 00:36:15,715
Our little Scout will be better for it.

634
00:36:18,885 --> 00:36:21,762
♪ I swore that I'd become ♪

635
00:36:21,846 --> 00:36:26,225
♪ A better man for you and I tried ♪

636
00:36:26,309 --> 00:36:28,769
♪ Tried to change my ways ♪

637
00:36:28,853 --> 00:36:32,064
♪ And walk the line you follow ♪

638
00:36:33,149 --> 00:36:35,735
♪ I bore a flame that burned ♪

639
00:36:35,818 --> 00:36:40,531
♪ A thousand suns for you but it died ♪

640
00:36:40,615 --> 00:36:45,578
♪ Told you I could never
Love somebody else ♪

641
00:36:45,661 --> 00:36:47,121
♪ But I lied ♪

642
00:36:47,205 --> 00:36:51,918
♪ Mm, I lied ♪

643
00:36:54,754 --> 00:36:59,634
♪ Mm, I lied ♪

644
00:36:59,717 --> 00:37:01,761
[Joe] The vigil was beautiful.

645
00:37:01,844 --> 00:37:03,054
The whole town came.

646
00:37:03,137 --> 00:37:06,224
Is he gonna come out? I don't get it.

647
00:37:07,475 --> 00:37:08,935
Is this some kind of strategy?

648
00:37:09,018 --> 00:37:11,229
[Joe] Sherry and Kiki
held out the longest,

649
00:37:11,312 --> 00:37:14,273
but that's so they could grab
the best flowers for a photo shoot.

650
00:37:14,357 --> 00:37:16,067
A Natalie tribute, of course.

651
00:37:16,150 --> 00:37:18,444
Tasteful as the day is long.

652
00:37:18,986 --> 00:37:20,029
Let's go. Come on.

653
00:37:20,112 --> 00:37:22,573
[Joe] I don't think Matthew wanted
to look even guiltier,

654
00:37:22,657 --> 00:37:25,243
but not showing up to your wife's vigil...

655
00:37:27,912 --> 00:37:29,372
-[man] Matthew.
-Matthew, sir.

656
00:37:29,455 --> 00:37:31,999
He's out. Come on. Let's go. Camera up.

657
00:37:33,417 --> 00:37:35,962
[man] ...ask you a couple
quick questions, Matthew?

658
00:37:36,045 --> 00:37:37,505
[ominous music playing]

659
00:37:41,884 --> 00:37:45,304
It would mean a lot to Natalie to see
how many people came out here.

660
00:37:46,639 --> 00:37:47,890
How many people care.

661
00:37:51,477 --> 00:37:53,479
[Joe] It wasn't a strategy.

662
00:37:53,562 --> 00:37:58,192
He waited so long
because he almost couldn't do it.

663
00:37:58,276 --> 00:38:00,278
It's that hard for him to talk about her.

664
00:38:00,945 --> 00:38:02,738
Because he cares.

665
00:38:02,822 --> 00:38:06,909
I am worried about my wife.
Natalie, if you're watching this,

666
00:38:07,743 --> 00:38:08,744
please come home.

667
00:38:09,745 --> 00:38:11,372
Or let me know you're okay.

668
00:38:12,248 --> 00:38:16,585
[Joe] The truth is, Matthew doesn't have
to go down for this.

669
00:38:17,962 --> 00:38:18,796
We need you.

670
00:38:22,133 --> 00:38:23,134
I need you.

671
00:38:27,847 --> 00:38:31,225
And if somebody out there
has done something to my wife...

672
00:38:33,394 --> 00:38:34,687
I will find you...

673
00:38:35,980 --> 00:38:37,481
and you will be punished.

674
00:38:41,861 --> 00:38:42,695
Thank you.

675
00:38:43,779 --> 00:38:45,948
[Goodwin]
Has your wife ever left you before?

676
00:38:46,032 --> 00:38:47,533
Have you notified her family?

677
00:38:47,616 --> 00:38:49,702
Matthew, anything to...

678
00:38:49,785 --> 00:38:50,953
[indistinct chatter]

679
00:38:52,413 --> 00:38:53,247
That's it?

680
00:38:53,331 --> 00:38:56,584
[Joe] Contrary to popular belief,
it's not always the husband.

681
00:38:56,667 --> 00:38:59,837
But we're not going down for this either.

682
00:39:01,380 --> 00:39:03,674
They've got nothing.
Even if they find something,

683
00:39:03,758 --> 00:39:05,092
we'll take care of it.

684
00:39:05,968 --> 00:39:07,511
We always do.

685
00:39:12,558 --> 00:39:14,268
[cell phone buzzing]

686
00:39:17,063 --> 00:39:18,105
Falco.

687
00:39:19,398 --> 00:39:20,483
We found the ring.

688
00:39:21,776 --> 00:39:22,735
Okay.

689
00:39:24,820 --> 00:39:28,157
[Joe] It's been said,
"Nothing ever happens in the suburbs."

690
00:39:29,575 --> 00:39:31,077
[doorbell rings]

691
00:39:33,746 --> 00:39:35,122
-Hey.
-Hey.

692
00:39:36,499 --> 00:39:40,878
It's an inadequate gesture
for making sure I didn't die last week.

693
00:39:40,961 --> 00:39:44,048
Unnecessary. Thank you.
I'm glad you're better.

694
00:39:45,257 --> 00:39:47,802
If you'll excuse me, I'm expecting a call.

695
00:39:52,139 --> 00:39:55,142
[Joe] Maybe it's more like,
"Nothing ever really changes."

696
00:39:56,936 --> 00:39:58,687
[pop music playing over speakers]

697
00:40:05,111 --> 00:40:06,153
[bells chiming]

698
00:40:07,738 --> 00:40:09,573
-Hey.
-You're not closed yet, are you?

699
00:40:09,657 --> 00:40:13,369
No, Gil, hey. You're just in time.
What can I get you?

700
00:40:14,453 --> 00:40:17,832
-How about half a dozen blueberry?
-Coming right up.

701
00:40:19,500 --> 00:40:21,585
Hey, I haven't seen Margaret.

702
00:40:21,669 --> 00:40:26,090
-Wanna tell her I said hi?
-Yeah, yeah, that's actually why I'm here.

703
00:40:26,841 --> 00:40:28,175
Margaret would have come too,

704
00:40:28,259 --> 00:40:31,887
but she took the girls to her mom's
while they're recovering.

705
00:40:31,971 --> 00:40:33,973
Oh. Were they sick?

706
00:40:34,056 --> 00:40:35,141
Not anymore.

707
00:40:35,766 --> 00:40:37,143
But they both had it.

708
00:40:37,810 --> 00:40:40,813
Can't tell you how sorry we are
for exposing Henry.

709
00:40:42,982 --> 00:40:44,984
Both your daughters had measles?

710
00:40:45,067 --> 00:40:48,028
Margaret really regrets not saying
anything when you called.

711
00:40:48,112 --> 00:40:51,323
She was just stunned to hear
that Henry had to be hospitalized.

712
00:40:51,407 --> 00:40:53,742
Our girls were pretty minor.

713
00:40:54,994 --> 00:40:57,204
We hope you won't hold it against us.

714
00:40:58,330 --> 00:41:01,542
You see, we just don't believe
in subjecting kids

715
00:41:01,625 --> 00:41:03,711
to toxic injections they don't need

716
00:41:03,794 --> 00:41:06,380
to fight things
their bodies were created to fight.

717
00:41:06,464 --> 00:41:09,842
We don't judge people who do, of course.

718
00:41:10,551 --> 00:41:14,263
Anyway, I-- Jeez.
I didn't come here to get on a soapbox.

719
00:41:14,346 --> 00:41:17,057
Again, we apologize.

720
00:41:17,725 --> 00:41:21,020
The most important thing is
that everyone is better now, right?

721
00:41:27,151 --> 00:41:27,985
Thanks.

722
00:41:33,491 --> 00:41:35,075
-Hey, Gil?
-Yep?

723
00:41:45,211 --> 00:41:46,754
[theme music playing]
